<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/711"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_711_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=4b2d49b000bb14fb6c2c81b9fce72fb1&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Virgin Radio logo" title="Virgin Radio logo" border="0" width="133" height="150" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2>Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050406075408/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/711">ECS improves broadcasting options for Virgin Radio</a></h3><p>The School of Electronics and Computer Science (ECS) at the University of Southampton is the first university department to deploy IPv6 in production on its network.  Now a team at the School has worked on the technology with Virgin Radio to vastly increase its listening capacity online.</p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

